Common Interview Mistakes
Mistake 1
Thinking retries are enough.
Retries solve availability.
They do not solve duplicate processing.


Mistake 2
Using timestamp as idempotency key.
Bad idea.
Two requests can have different timestamps.


Mistake 3
Not storing response.
Good systems store:

Idempotency Key
Response
Status
So duplicate requests get identical responses.


One-Line Definition
	Idempotency is a design principle where executing the same operation multiple times produces the same final state as executing it once, typically achieved using unique request identifiers called Idempotency Keys to prevent duplicate processing in distributed systems.
